org.openbase.bco.ontology.lib.manager.aggregation.datatype

Class OntStateChange.AggregatedContinuous

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openbase.bco.ontology.lib.manager.aggregation.datatype.OntStateChange.AggregatedContinuous
  • Enclosing class:
    OntStateChange<T>

    public static class OntStateChange.AggregatedContinuous
extends Object
    This subclass defines an concrete instance/type of a state change of OntStateChange. It should be used, if the state change was manipulated as far (already aggregated) and the state value(s) based on continuous value(s) (e.g. numbers like hsb).

    • Constructor Detail

      • AggregatedContinuous

        public AggregatedContinuous(String mean,
                            String variance,
                            String standardDeviation,
                            String timeWeighting,
                            String quantity,
                            org.apache.jena.rdf.model.RDFNode stateValue)
                     throws org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException
        Constructor creates an continuous state change instance, which based on manipulated (already aggregated) state values (e.g. numbers like hsb) to store them. The information parts (input argument) will be convert to specific data types (see getter of this class).
        Parameters:
        mean - of all state values from the same source, which are stored about the aggregated time frame. Lossy Statistical information.
        variance - of all state values from the same source, which are stored about the aggregated time frame. Lossy Statistical information.
        standardDeviation - of all state values from the same source, which are stored about the aggregated time frame. Lossy Statistical information.
        timeWeighting - is the indicator how long the unit keeps connection to the system with value range [0..1]. E.g. an value of 0.6 means that there was connection (and observed state changes) in 60% of the aggregated time frame. 40% of the time was not observed so that this value is used as inaccuracy.
        quantity - is the number of activation of the based state value source in the aggregated time frame.
        stateValue - is the specific continuous state value.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException - is thrown in case at least one input parameter is null/invalid or the state value isn't a literal (continuous value).
